WEBVTT

00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:04.200
Alright! Your app is running, so let's actually work

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:06.600
with it. Three commands cover the daily loop.

00:00:07.499 --> 00:00:10.299
Tunnel opens your app in a browser, term runs

00:00:10.299 --> 00:00:12.859
commands inside the sandbox, and sync

00:00:12.859 --> 00:00:15.499
moves files in and out. That's

00:00:15.499 --> 00:00:17.019
the whole daily workflow.

00:00:20.481 --> 00:00:23.121
First, the tunnel command. The app runs

00:00:23.121 --> 00:00:25.761
on the server, not your laptop. The tunnel

00:00:25.761 --> 00:00:28.721
command forwards a container port over SSH

00:00:29.041 --> 00:00:31.441
so you can open it at localhost in your browser.

00:00:34.557 --> 00:00:37.197
Port forwarded. The app is now reachable at

00:00:37.197 --> 00:00:37.917
localhost.

00:00:38.483 --> 00:00:39.686
With the tunnel running,

00:00:39.686 --> 00:00:41.792
the app opens right in your browser.

00:00:41.792 --> 00:00:43.597
For this demo we load rediacc.com,

00:00:43.597 --> 00:00:46.305
the same way you would reach your own app

00:00:46.305 --> 00:00:47.809
served straight from the container.

00:00:50.896 --> 00:00:53.536
Second, the term command. The terminal

00:00:53.536 --> 00:00:56.736
connect command drops you into the repo sandbox

00:00:57.136 --> 00:01:00.176
, the same isolated view as VS Code. Run

00:01:00.176 --> 00:01:02.736
any command against this repo Docker daemon

00:01:02.736 --> 00:01:04.096
without leaving your terminal.

00:01:06.297 --> 00:01:09.017
Inside the repo sandbox. Run anything

00:01:09.017 --> 00:01:10.537
as if you were SSH'd in.

00:01:13.961 --> 00:01:16.521
Now we will move files. First a dry

00:01:16.521 --> 00:01:19.161
-run preview. It shows exactly what would

00:01:19.161 --> 00:01:22.121
change without copying anything. Always preview

00:01:22.121 --> 00:01:23.081
when you are not sure.

00:01:26.209 --> 00:01:28.289
Preview only. No files moved yet.

00:01:31.965 --> 00:01:34.925
And the upload for real. The sync upload command

00:01:34.925 --> 00:01:37.725
moves files from your laptop into the repo

00:01:37.805 --> 00:01:41.005
over SSH, with rsync delta compression

00:01:41.405 --> 00:01:44.285
. Tunnel, term, sync. Three commands

00:01:44.285 --> 00:01:45.245
cover the daily loop.

00:01:47.695 --> 00:01:50.335
Files uploaded. Delta compression handles

00:01:50.335 --> 00:01:51.215
big trees.

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:54.790
And that's the daily three. See

00:01:54.790 --> 00:01:55.830
you in the next one!
